interpretation: The "calendar" card represents the passage of time, organization, and planning. It reminds us to be mindful of deadlines and appointments, and to prioritize our responsibilities. This card can indicate a need for structure and routine in our lives, or a warning that we may be overcommitting ourselves. It can also signify the importance of keeping track of our progress and accomplishments, and celebrating our successes. When this card appears, take a moment to reflect on your goals and priorities, and consider how you can best manage your time to achieve them. Keywords associated with this card include deadlines, scheduling, routines, milestones, and achievements.
